Environment setting:

1.Laravel
install: https://laravel.com/docs/5.4/installation

	(1)Install Composer(if you have already install it. Skip)
		(1.1)Go to https://getcomposer.org/download/ and follow it’s instruction.
	(2)Then, you can use ‘composer global require "laravel/installer"’ in terminal to install Laravel.
	(3)Enter ‘sudo vim etc/paths’ to modify doc. Add ‘$HOME/.composer/vendor/bin’ line at bottom and then exit(Can see at https://laravel.com/docs/5.4#server-requirements).
	(4)Remember to run ’source /etc/paths’ to soure the $PATH
	(5)Remember to reopen the terminal 
	(6)Finish



